<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Powell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-19"><hi rend="italic">May 19,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Powell inquires if he may take the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Topeka</hi> to St. Marc to consult with the commander of the army
                            of the north and advise him not to go to Port au Prince. He states that
                            if the army, which is said to number 5,000 men, is not prevented from
                            reaching Port au Prince, a severe contest is to be expected, in which
                            American interests will suffer.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>